article.headline: Colgate 54, Lafayette 51
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Willie Morse made four late free throws and Jon Simon scored 15 points, leading Colgate to a 54-51 victory over Lafayette on Wednesday night. Kyle Chones finished with 11 points and 11 rebounds for Colgate (9-14, 4-6 Patriot League), which snapped a three-game losing streak against the Leopards (8-16, 2-7). Bilal Abdullah scored 14 points, Ted Detmer had 12 points and 12 rebounds, and Andrew Brown finished with 10 points for Lafayette. Detmer hit a pair of free throws with 2:51 left to pull Colgate within three points, and Abdullah hit a free throw that closed the gap to two points with 21 seconds remaining. Morse, who scored six points in the game, hit four shots from the line in the final minute, including two with five seconds remaining before Brown's 3-point shot at the buzzer fell short as time expired.
